f=AI & Agents/proto/operational/commands/proto-commands.md · h1:proto — Command Triggers=\| Trigger phrases \| Skill \| Shortcut \| · h1:proto — Command Triggers=\|---\|---\|---\| · h1:proto — Command Triggers=\| "prototype agent", "test new agent", "spin up an experiment", "scaffold", "cage check" \| agent-prototype-kit \| /proto \| · h1:proto — Command Triggers=\| "success criteria", "define the eval", "what does success mean", "baseline" \| eval-first-design \| /criteria \| · h1:proto — Command Triggers=\| "verdict", "expiry", "promote", "archive", "extend the prototype" \| promote-or-archive-verdict \| /verdict \| · h1:proto — Command Triggers=\| "quick prototype", "what fidelity", "paper prototype", "timebox", "scope creep" \| rapid-prototyping-method \| /fidelity \| · h2:Precedence=expired prototype outranks everything (verdict before new scaffolds). Criteria (eval-first-design) before any build question /proto without frozen criteria bounces /criteria. "Extend" routes promote-or-archive-verdict (extension Rail exception, once), never quietly kit.